Rating: 3
Mid-winter farmer's markets are only providing mature curly kale. I followed the recipe with a couple of adjustments to accommodate the less tender kale. One was tear the kale into pieces off the stems. The second was to cook the leaves briefly in simmering water, until they were bright green, and then shock them in cold water. I also let the salad marinate in the dressing for several hours before serving. It was well-received and my husband gave it two thumbs up.

