Rating: 4
This is a staple in our home now and friends always ask for the recipe. It is extremely versatile in that you can substitute other cheese, nuts and fruit with many different others (I used dried wild blueberries once - great). I also use any vinegar- based vinaigrette since it's the vinegar that "cooks" the kale. Just make sure you've let it sit in the vinaigrette long enough - you can tell by taste. I never use the honey or the rice wine vinegar because it seems to make the salad too sweet. I use any kind of kale except for dinosaur/lacinato. So so healthy and delicious, it's a main meal with roasted fish or meat on top, or even a poached egg with a dollop of aioli.

Rating: 4
Excellent salad! Always get requests for the recipe. Packed with nutrition. My diet avoids sugars and dairy so I modify the recipe as such: Use Toasted Sesame Oil instead of Olive; Omit salt, honey, and cheese; Add Nutritional Yeast if in a cheesy mood; I soak the currants in a small vessel with just enough vinegar to cover them. Kale is quite sturdy so I often toss the ingredients before work and have the salad with lunch, several hours later. It's not a problem, as the longer it marinates, the easier to digest but still hardy vs. limp.

